Oh, Memphis, he's gorgeous.

180
00:11:39,090 --> 00:11:41,790
可不是吗？ 看看你
Isn't he, though? Look at you.

181
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:43,950
我给你带了东西
I got something for you.

182
00:11:44,130 --> 00:11:45,860
张开嘴
Open up.

183
00:11:49,370 --> 00:11:52,060
哦，我就喜欢看你喂食的样子
Oh, I love the way she does that.

184
00:11:55,570 --> 00:11:57,510
W，X，Y和Z
W, X, Y and Z

185
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:58,870
早上好，同学们
Good morning, class.

186
00:11:59,040 --> 00:12:01,410
早上好，维奥拉小姐
Good morning, Miss Viola.

187
00:12:01,580 --> 00:12:02,570
好的
Right.

188
00:12:02,750 --> 00:12:06,150
那么，今天我们要上企鹅小学里
Well, today we begin with the most important lesson you will ever learn...

189
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,610
最重要的一堂课
...at Penguin Elementary.

190
00:12:07,790 --> 00:12:09,450
有谁知道是什么吗？
Does anyone know what that is?

191
00:12:09,620 --> 00:12:10,880
谁知道？谁知道？
Anyone? Anyone?

192
00:12:11,060 --> 00:12:12,040
谁？西摩？
Someone? Seymour?

193
00:12:12,220 --> 00:12:14,120
钓鱼吗？ 不是
Fishing? No.

194
00:12:14,290 --> 00:12:15,660
曼波？
Mumble?

195
00:12:15,830 --> 00:12:17,420
不要吃黄色的雪？
Don't eat yellow snow?

196
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,990
不，不是的
No, that's not it, no.

197
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:22,330
是心灵之歌，小姐 谢谢你，葛露亚，好极了，没错
It's our Heartsong, Miss. Thank you, Gloria. Excellent, yes.

198
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:25,370
没有心灵之歌，我们就不能称为真正的企鹅 大家说对不对？
Without our Heartsong, we can't be truly penguin, can we?

199
00:12:25,540 --> 00:12:27,330
对
No.

200
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:30,870
但是，亲爱的孩子们 事实上这不是我可以教会你们的
But, my dears, it's not something that I can actually teach you.

201
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:33,440
有人知道为什么吗？ 谁知道，谁知道？
Does anybody know why? Anyone? Anyone?

202
00:12:33,610 --> 00:12:35,270
你之所以不能教给我们，夫人…
You can't teach it to us, ma'am...

203
00:12:35,450 --> 00:12:39,080
…是因为心灵之歌必须由我们自己去寻找
...because we have to find our Heartsongs all by ourselves.

204
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:40,240
说得好
Well done, you.

205
00:12:40,420 --> 00:12:42,080
这是你在内心深处所听到的…
It's the voice you hear inside...

206
00:12:42,250 --> 00:12:43,840
…真正的自我
...who you truly are.

207
00:12:44,020 --> 00:12:46,550
对，谢谢你，葛露亚 好极了，谢谢你
Yes. Thank you, Gloria. Excellent, lovely, thank you.

208
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:49,090
那现在让我们安静一下
So let's all be very still now.

209
00:12:49,260 --> 00:12:52,520
等一会儿，你就会感受得到
Take a moment and let it come to you.

210
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:53,790
我听到了！ 我来
I got one! Pick me!

211
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:56,900
我来！我来！ 一次一个，西摩，你先来
Pick me! Pick me! One at a time. Yes, Seymour.

212
00:12:57,070 --> 00:13:01,200
别再逼我，我已快要发疯
Don't push me 'Cause I am close to the edge

213
00:13:01,370 --> 00:13:04,310
我不想让毛掉光
I'm trying not to lose my head

214
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:07,440
嗯，我喜欢 听起来让我觉得很美，亲爱的
Yes, I like that one. I could really get jiggy with that. Lovely.

215
00:13:07,610 --> 00:13:09,200
我准备好了，我听到了
I'm ready. I got one.

216
00:13:09,380 --> 00:13:11,940
噢，我想也是，葛露亚
Oh, I thought you might, Gloria.

217
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:17,820
夜色如此曼妙
Midnight creeps so slowly

218
00:13:17,990 --> 00:13:20,420
慢慢撒进那些
Into hearts of those

219
00:13:20,590 --> 00:13:23,190
依然渴望的心灵里
Who need more than they get

220
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:26,260
白昼的赌局
Daylight deals a bad hand

221
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:35,060
下注太多的企鹅 一手烂牌
To a penguin. Who has laid too many bets

222
00:13:35,410 --> 00:13:37,030
我只能想到这么多了
That's as far as I got so far.

223
00:13:37,210 --> 00:13:39,800
噢，好，太好了，真的太棒了 棒极了
Oh, yes, lovely. Really lovely. That's beautiful.

224
00:13:39,980 --> 00:13:43,240
曼波，看起来你等不及想和大家分享了
Well, Mumble, since you seem so keen to share.

225
00:13:44,050 --> 00:13:47,980
我想唱的是“砰”的一声，然后…
Mine's sort of a boom and a:

226
00:13:50,690 --> 00:13:51,990
又是“砰”的一声
And another boom.

227
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:53,280
这就是你在心里听到的？
You heard that in there?

228
00:13:53,460 --> 00:13:56,120
你喜欢吗？ 哦！这不成旋律
Do you like it? I'm afraid that's not a tune.

229
00:13:56,190 --> 00:14:00,150
不算？ 是的，亲爱的，旋律应该是这样的
It's not? No, dear. A tune is like:

230
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:05,630
哦，好的
Oh, okay.

231
00:14:10,410 --> 00:14:11,670
那是谁？
Who is that?

232
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:14,680
他是孟菲斯和诺玛・珍的孩子
That is the offspring of Memphis and Norma Jean.

233
00:14:14,850 --> 00:14:16,400
一只小袋鼠 （小袋鼠：四五十年代的一个卡通角色）
The wee hippity-hopper.

234
00:14:22,820 --> 00:14:24,810
这不好笑！
It's not funny!

235
00:14:24,990 --> 00:14:27,010
对，对，一点也不好笑
No. No, not in the least.

236
00:14:27,190 --> 00:14:30,650
没有心灵之歌的企鹅很难算是企鹅
A penguin without a Heartsong is hardly a penguin at all.

237
00:14:30,830 --> 00:14:33,260
他把我耳朵都震坏了
I think he broke my ear.

238
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,130
这么多年了，我从来没，我是说…
In all my years, I've never, I mean...

239
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:39,900
而且你的声音这么好 哎，太奇怪了
And you having such fine voices. Well, it's bizarre.

240
00:14:40,070 --> 00:14:43,600
发生过什么事吗？我是指早期发育的时候
Did anything happen, you know, during early development?

241
00:14:43,770 --> 00:14:46,210
没有，一切都很好，很正常的孵化
No, all fine. Normal incubation.

242
00:14:46,380 --> 00:14:47,710
好 是吧，亲爱的？
Right. Wasn't it, honey?

243
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:51,470
对，对，我想可能是这个冬天太寒冷了
Yeah. Yeah, it was a tough winter, I guess.

244
00:14:51,650 --> 00:14:52,640
没错，没错
Right, right.

245
00:14:52,820 --> 00:14:55,280
不过他的确比较晚才孵出来… 嗯，我理解
He did hatch a little late... Yes, I understand. Yes.

246
00:14:55,450 --> 00:14:58,510
一想到他会孤独一生… 小声点，小声点
To think he might spend his life alone... Quite, quite.

247
00:14:58,690 --> 00:15:00,850
…永远都不会遇到真爱
...never to meet his one true love.

248
00:15:01,020 --> 00:15:04,220
噢，拜托，维奥拉小姐 我们可以做什么吗？
Oh, please, Miss Viola, isn't there something we can do?

249
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:07,850
嗯，幸好还有爱丝特坎太太
Well, there is always Mrs. Astrakhan.

250
00:15:08,030 --> 00:15:09,020
爱丝特坎太太？
Mrs. Astrakhan?

251
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:11,960
只要是能办到的事 爱丝特坎太太都能办到
If anyone can, Mrs. Astrakhan can.

252
00:15:16,340 --> 00:15:17,570
不会唱歌？
Can't sing?

253
00:15:17,740 --> 00:15:20,010
不会唱歌？ 真失败，亲爱的
Can't sing? Rubbish, darling.

254
00:15:20,180 --> 00:15:22,810
每只小企鹅都有一支心灵之歌
Every little penguin has a song.

255
00:15:22,980 --> 00:15:24,610
教会你以后…
When I have finished...

256
00:15:24,780 --> 00:15:28,450
…你的歌声会让每个人起鸡皮疙瘩
...your singing will be giving everyone the goose pimple.

257
00:15:28,620 --> 00:15:32,520
好，现在开始 首先，我们必须找到一种感觉
Now, to begin. First, we must find a feeling.

258
00:15:32,690 --> 00:15:35,820
开心的感觉，伤心的感觉
Happy feeling, sad feeling.

259
00:15:35,990 --> 00:15:39,330
也或许是孤独的感觉
Maybe lonely feeling.

260
00:15:39,830 --> 00:15:41,700
你感觉到了吗？
You feel it?

261
00:15:41,870 --> 00:15:44,890
好的，现在唱出来吧
Good. Now, let it out.

262
00:15:45,070 --> 00:15:47,760
要自然
Be spontaneous.

263
00:15:51,710 --> 00:15:53,010
那，那是什么？
That, what is that?

264
00:15:53,180 --> 00:15:55,370
我觉得很自然啊
I'm being spontan-you-us.

265
00:15:56,810 --> 00:15:59,650
亲爱的，你想和美丽的女孩约会吗？
Darling, you want to meet beautiful girl?

266
00:15:59,820 --> 00:16:01,180
你想要蛋宝宝吗？
You want to make the egg?

267
00:16:01,350 --> 00:16:02,440
哦，想啊
Oh, yes.

268
00:16:02,620 --> 00:16:08,020
那就唱！不要晃来晃去，别乱动
Well, sing! And no jiggy-jog. Do not move muscle.

269
00:16:08,190 --> 00:16:10,320
呆在原地！
No moving!

270
00:16:11,090 --> 00:16:14,530
一闪，一闪，亮晶晶
Twinkle, twinkle, little star

271
00:16:15,230 --> 00:16:16,290
够了！
Enough!

272
00:16:16,470 --> 00:16:19,660
好，我们重头开始
Okay. We go back to the top.

273
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:23,760
忘记身体，用内心来感受
Forget body. Look inside soul.

274
00:16:23,940 --> 00:16:27,640
感受那种感情，强烈的感情
Feel the feeling. Enormous feeling.

275
00:16:27,810 --> 00:16:31,180
它是如此强烈，充满了你的身体
So enormous it fills whole body.

276
00:16:31,350 --> 00:16:34,610
它必须被释放出来，否则你就会爆炸
It must escape or you explode.

277
00:16:34,790 --> 00:16:37,620
现在，张开你的小嘴 快啊
Now, open your little beak. Come on.

278
00:16:37,790 --> 00:16:40,920
对，对，抬起头来，就这样
Yes, yes. Lift up the head, that's it.

279
00:16:41,090 --> 00:16:43,390
现在，现在…
Now... Now...

280
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:48,260
就现在！
Now

281
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:19,530
鬼啊！太恐怖了！
Disaster! Catastrophe!

282
00:17:19,700 --> 00:17:21,960
我从没有失败过
I never fail before.

283
00:17:22,130 --> 00:17:25,260
从来没有，从来没有！
Never! Never!

284
00:17:34,040 --> 00:17:37,310
不过，这样也挺可爱的 但企鹅不能这样，知道吗？
Well, I thought it was kind of cute. But it just ain't penguin, okay?

285
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:40,750
那他要是就是有点不一样呢？ 我一直就喜欢有点与众不同
So what if he's a little different? I always kind of liked different.

286
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:43,580
他跟别人没什么不一样的 就是一只普通的帝企鹅
He's not different. He's a regular emperor penguin.

287
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:45,780
嘿，知道吗？我可以不去上学
Hey, you know what? I can leave school.

288
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:48,150
我可以去干活，我们一家三口一起
I can go to work. The three of us.

289
00:17:48,330 --> 00:17:52,160
哦，小朋友 在你接受完教育之前哪里也不要去
Whoa, little fella. You ain't going nowhere till you got yourself an education.

290
00:17:52,330 --> 00:17:55,260
你要学会唱的有力而响亮，知道吗？
You get them singing muscles big and strong, you got that?

291
00:17:55,430 --> 00:17:56,560
我会努力的，爸爸
I'll try, Pa.

292
00:17:56,730 --> 00:18:00,230
你最好如此 成功的第一个字是成，第二个字是…
You bet you will. The word "triumph" starts with "try," and it ends with...

293
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:04,070
“功” 没错，大大的“功”字
"Umph." That's right. A great big "umph."

294
00:18:04,840 --> 00:18:06,400
我要去捕鱼了
I'm going fishing.

295
00:18:12,350 --> 00:18:14,540
噢，曼波
Oh, Mumble.

296
00:18:18,290 --> 00:18:20,720
那是第一个艰难的夏天
That first hard summer...

297
00:18:20,890 --> 00:18:23,920
当他的爸爸妈妈在家和大海之间来回奔波…
...while his mom and dad were working overtime...

298
00:18:24,090 --> 00:18:27,000
…加班加点工作时…
...on the great commute to the sea...

299
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:31,500
…曼波找到了一个可以远离菲薄…
...Mumble found a place away from disapproving eyes...

300
00:18:31,670 --> 00:18:37,130
…尽情展现自我的地方
...where a funky little fella could be himself.

301
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:34,230
嘿，你在那儿干嘛呢，带蹼的鸟？
Hey, what you doing there, flipper bird?

302
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:36,630
没事，你们在干嘛呢？
Nothing. What are you doing?

303
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:39,630
没事，路过吃点午饭而已
Nothing. Just dropped in for a little lunch.

304
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:42,530
有吃的？这里？
There's food? Here?

305
00:19:43,070 --> 00:19:44,630
腿还是翅膀？
Leg or wing?

306
00:19:44,810 --> 00:19:47,240
不不不，等等，不会是我吧，我是企鹅啊
Oh, no, no, wait. Not me, I'm a penguin.

307
00:19:47,410 --> 00:19:51,110
一点没错，带蹼的鸟 就是你，吃鱼的家伙
Exactly. The flipper birds, that's you, eat the fish.

308
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:54,810
会飞的鸟，也就是我 吃的是带蹼的鸟和鱼
The flying birds, that's me, eat the flipper bird and the fish.

309
00:19:54,990 --> 00:19:57,220
但最近，没什么鱼吃了
And lately, there ain't a lot of fish.

310
00:19:57,390 --> 00:19:59,480
所以… 这次我要吃有汁的那块
So... This time I'm getting the juicy bits.

311
00:19:59,660 --> 00:20:02,060
我先来！ 嘿，你要和我抢？
Me first! Hey, you want a piece of me?

312
00:20:02,230 --> 00:20:04,890
嘿嘿嘿，我在考虑午饭的事情
Hey, hey, hey! I'm trying to think about lunch.

313
00:20:05,060 --> 00:20:08,260
等等！看看这个！
Wait! Watch this!

314
00:20:13,540 --> 00:20:18,630
嗯，是挺奇怪的，好吧，你听着 我就破一次例，文明地解决这件事
Yeah, that's weird, all right. Listen. For once, we're gonna do this civilized.

315
00:20:18,810 --> 00:20:21,500
现在，准备好… 嘿！你腿上那是什么？
Now, get in line... Hey! What's that on your leg?

316
00:20:21,580 --> 00:20:24,710
什么？这个小东西？ 哦，天，别跟他提那个
What? This little thing? Oh, no. Don't start him on that.

317
00:20:24,880 --> 00:20:28,010
闭嘴！这只小蹼鸟问了我一个很敏感的问题
Shut up! The little flipper bird asked me a perceptive question.

318
00:20:28,190 --> 00:20:30,880
一个必须给出答案的问题 又来了
A question like that deserves an answer. Here we go.

319
00:20:31,050 --> 00:20:32,720
我送你两个词：
I got two words for you:

320
00:20:33,390 --> 00:20:35,950
异形绑架
"Alien abduction."

321
00:20:36,130 --> 00:20:37,820
噢，你得继续问了 可怜啊
Oh, you had to ask. Have mercy.

322
00:20:37,990 --> 00:20:39,860
安静！
Quiet!

323
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:43,430
小朋友，这世上有一种东西
Now, little buddy, there is something out there.

324
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:45,690
一种生物，跟我们不一样的生物
Creatures. Not like us.

325
00:20:45,870 --> 00:20:48,100
更大，更凶猛，当然也更聪明
Bigger, fiercer, and smarter too.

326
00:20:48,270 --> 00:20:49,760
问我是怎么知道的 你怎么知道？
Ask me how I know. How?

327
00:20:49,940 --> 00:20:52,100
因为我被他们捉到过，这就是原因
Because I've been captured by them, that's how.

328
00:20:52,280 --> 00:20:53,300
难以置信
Unbelievable.

329
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:55,450
“难以置信”什么意思？ 这就是事实
What do you mean "unbelievable?" It's true.

330
00:20:55,610 --> 00:20:57,840
当时我正坐在石头上，干自己的事…
I'm sitting on a rock, minding my own business...

331
00:20:58,010 --> 00:20:59,610
…突然间，他们就来到了我头顶上
...when suddenly, they're onto me.

332
00:20:59,780 --> 00:21:01,910
那些生物，长得跟丑陋的大企鹅似的
These beings, like big ugly penguins.

333
00:21:02,090 --> 00:21:04,210
又肥又胖，松弛的脸上正面安着一双眼睛
Fat, flabby faces with front-ways eyes...

334
00:21:04,390 --> 00:21:07,790
…没羽毛，没有喙 还有这个看来像附属品的东西
...no feathers, no beaks, and these... These appendages.

335
00:21:08,130 --> 00:21:10,650
他们为了检查我，把我绑了起来
They probe me. They tie me up. They strap me down.

336
00:21:10,830 --> 00:21:13,690
然后拿出一个尖尖的东西插进我身体
They take this pointy thing and they stick it into me.

337
00:21:13,860 --> 00:21:16,420
再然后，我就晕了过去
And then, blackout.

338
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:18,000
天呐
Gosh.

339
00:21:18,170 --> 00:21:21,100
我醒来之后 就在腿上发现了这个…这个东西
I woke up and there's this... This thing on me.

340
00:21:21,270 --> 00:21:25,500
每只会飞的鸟都鄙视我，说 “嘿，发生什么了，黄腿？”
Every flying bird is dissing me, "Hey, what's happening, yellow leg?"

341
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:27,670
真是对我的羞辱
It was humiliating.

342
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:29,000
然后呢？
And then what?

343
00:21:29,180 --> 00:21:32,210
它们羞辱我，还不够么？
It was humiliating. What more do you want?

344
00:21:33,220 --> 00:21:35,340
